   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the customer requirement it is possible to have different
types of module configurations, with or without redundancy. N + 0,
N + 1 and N + x module configurations use one input source. </p>
      <p platform="Modular-DC Modular-AC" class="- topic/p ">A 2N rectifier module configuration
uses two independent rectifier mains.</p>
      <p platform="Modular-DCDC-Converter" class="- topic/p ">A 2N DC/DC converter module configuration
uses two independent DC inputs.</p>
      <p platform="Modular-AC" class="- topic/p ">For a UPS system it is possible to have one
module configuration for the inverters and another for the rectifier
modules. 2N is only possible for rectifier modules.</p>
      <note class="- topic/note ">N stands for the number of modules required to supply the full
load that the system is designed for.</note>
